      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "i tried the bedding procedure like you said but the squeal is still there and it honestly sounds so weird... like it's coming from deep inside the wheel well. it's such an erratic, sudden noise. do you think it could be something loose or bouncing around in there, or maybe a piece of debris caught in the brake shield?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sudden, erratic noise originating deep in the wheel well strongly suggests something loose, not just a pad issue. It's very possible that a piece of debris, like a small pebble or a shard of metal, has settled between the rotor and the brake shield. Have a close look inside the caliper assembly while spinning the wheel slowly; make sure the metal brake shield isn't vibrating or touching anything when the wheel rotates. If you locate any loose hardware or debris, removal should quiet the annoying shriek immediately.",
      "source": "target",
